	(16,1,'2015-08-15 14:11:42','2015-08-15 14:11:42','<h2>About Hayley Munguia</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-25\" src=\"http://hemdash.dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/hayley-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"hayley\" />Hayley Munguia is a data reporter and social media editor at <a href=\"http://fivethirtyeight.com/contributors/hayley-munguia/\" target=\"_blank\">FiveThirtyEight</a>. Previously, she worked for <a href=\"http://theweek.com/authors/hayley-munguia\" target=\"_blank\">TheWeek.com</a>, where she wrote commentary about international news and business. Before that, she was based in Tel Aviv, where she reported for <a href=\"http://hemdash.dev/publications/jerusalem-post/\">The Jerusalem Post</a> and wrote a column for the Austin-American Statesman.\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Her alma mater is New York University, where she studied New Media Journalism while editing and reporting for <a href=\"http://nyulocal.com/author/hayley-munguia/\" target=\"_blank\">NYU Local</a>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">When not writing, she likes to read, travel and admire other people’s dogs from afar.</p>','Home','','publish','open','open','','home','','','2015-08-16 13:45:37','2015-08-16 13:45:37','',0,'http://hemdash.dev/?page_id=16',0,'page','',0),
