	(26,1,'2015-08-16 13:15:23','2015-08-16 13:15:23','<h2><a href=\"http://hemdash.dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/hayley.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-25 size-medium\" src=\"http://hemdash.dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/hayley-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"hayley\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>About Hayley Munguia</h2>\n<p class=\"p1\">Hayley Munguia is a data reporter and social media editor at <a href=\"http://fivethirtyeight.com/contributors/hayley-munguia/\" target=\"_blank\">FiveThirtyEight</a>. Previously, she worked for <a href=\"http://theweek.com/authors/hayley-munguia\" target=\"_blank\">TheWeek.com</a>, where she wrote commentary about international news and business. Before that, she was based in Tel Aviv, where she reported for <a href=\"http://hemdash.dev/publications/jerusalem-post/\">The Jerusalem Post</a> and wrote a column for the Austin-American Statesman.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Her alma mater is New York University, where she studied New Media Journalism while editing and reporting for NYU Local.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">When not writing, she likes to read, travel and admire other people’s dogs from afar.</p>','Home','','inherit','open','open','','16-autosave-v1','','','2015-08-16 13:15:23','2015-08-16 13:15:23','',16,'http://hemdash.dev/16-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
